(43, 14, 22, 42, 6, 16, 16, NULL, 'Connection of Judas Figures', 'This connection highlights the presence of two distinct Judases in the New Testament. John 14:22 refers to Judas, not Iscariot, while Luke 6:16 identifies both Judas Iscariot and Judas the brother of James, emphasizing the need for clarity in distinguishing between them.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 14, 22, 44, 1, 13, 13, 'manifest thyself unto us', 'Disciples'' Understanding of Jesus', 'This connection highlights the theme of the disciples'' relationship with Jesus. In John 14:22, Judas questions how Jesus will reveal himself, while Acts 1:13 lists the disciples who continued to seek him after his resurrection.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 14, 22, 40, 10, 3, 3, NULL, 'Connection of Discipleship and Revelation', 'This connection highlights the theme of discipleship, as both passages reference the disciples of Jesus. In John 14:22, Judas (not Iscariot) seeks understanding of Jesus'' revelation, while Matthew 10:3 lists the disciples who are called to follow Him.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 14, 22, 41, 3, 18, 18, NULL, 'Discipleship and Revelation', 'This connection highlights the theme of discipleship, as both passages involve the disciples of Jesus. John 14:22 reflects the disciples'' desire for understanding of Jesus'' revelation, while Mark 3:18 lists those who were chosen to follow Him.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 14, 22, 43, 3, 4, 4, 'manifest thyself unto us', 'Understanding Spiritual Revelation', 'This connection highlights the theme of understanding spiritual truths. Both passages emphasize the difficulty of grasping deeper spiritual concepts, as seen in Judas''s question about manifestation and Nicodemus''s confusion about rebirth.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 14, 22, 43, 6, 60, 60, 'how is it that thou wilt manifest', 'Understanding Jesus'' Revelation', 'This connection highlights the difficulty of understanding Jesus'' teachings. In both passages, the disciples express confusion about how Jesus reveals himself and the nature of his message.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 14, 22, 44, 10, 40, 41, 'manifest thyself unto us', 'Manifestation to Chosen Witnesses', 'This connection highlights the theme of selective revelation. In John 14:22, the question of how Jesus will manifest himself to his followers, and not to the world, parallels Acts 10:40-41, which states that Jesus was shown to chosen witnesses, not to all people.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
